"title": "8803: pride, evil of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8803",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Pride is viewed as a great evil because it involves pretending to a greatness and glory that belong rightly to God alone.</p>\n<h2>The sinfulness of pride</h2>\n<h3>It is condemned as evil</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:23\">1SA 15:23</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:4\">PRO 21:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:16\">JAS 4:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:22-Mark7:23\">MRK 7:22–7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:29-Rom1:30\">ROM 1:29–1:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor12:20\">2CO 12:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:1-2Tim3:2\">2TI 3:1–3:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:16\">1JN 2:16</a></p>\n<h3>It is a characteristic of Satan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:2\">EZK 28:2</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:6\">1TI 3:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:4\">2TH 2:4</a> <em>the antichrist</em></p>\n<h2>Warnings against pride</h2>\n<h3>In the book of Proverbs</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:5\">PRO 16:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:18\">PRO 16:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:7\">PRO 3:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:34\">PRO 3:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:16-Prov6:17\">PRO 6:16–6:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:2\">PRO 11:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:6-Prov25:7\">PRO 25:6–25:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:27\">PRO 25:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov26:12\">PRO 26:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov27:1\">PRO 27:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:23\">PRO 29:23</a></p>\n<h3>Elsewhere in Scripture</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:21\">PSA 119:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:191\">LEV 26:191</a>SA <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:3\">2:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps12:2-Ps12:3\">PSA 12:2–12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:23-Jer9:24\">JER 9:23–9:24</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:5\">PSA 5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:4\">PSA 40:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps138:6\">PSA 138:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:21\">ISA 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:15-Jer13:17\">JER 13:15–13:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:12\">MAT 23:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:11\">LUK 14:11</a> <em>Jesus Christ's teaching on pride</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:16\">ROM 12:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:121\">1CO 10:121</a>PE <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:5\">5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:6\">JAS 4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov3:34\">PRO 3:34</a></p>\n<h2>The gospel excludes pride</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:27\">ROM 3:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:9-Luke18:14\">LUK 18:9–18:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom4:2-Rom4:3\">ROM 4:2–4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:17-Rom11:20\">ROM 11:17–11:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:26-1Cor1:31\">1CO 1:26–1:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:8-Eph2:9\">EPH 2:8–2:9</a></p>\n<h2>Godliness involves rejecting pride</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:13\">PRO 8:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps101:5\">PSA 101:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps131:1\">PSA 131:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:3\">ROM 12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:4\">1CO 13:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:14\">GAL 6:14</a></p>",
